<br>
*sits at the middle table in the common room of the Keep<br>
<br>
* pulls out a tattered parchment and a small travel quill<br>
<br>
*stares into space lost in memories almost forgotten<br>
<br>
Hail Knights! Welcome to the Cleric Chronicles of Senben Strongfaith Knight of Freedom. How to start this .... I was born ...no... so there I was .... nope ... It was on the day of my third heal that a human in bright armor and of Holy resolve came to me in the Evil Keep of the Crushbone Orcs speaking of a group of adventurers who were traveling the world laying to rest the walking dead and freeing the oppressed. His name was Adjantis Honorblade Knight of Marr. Upon inviting me to join him and his friends in there holy quest he took me to the city of Kelethin where another Holy Knight of Marr named Dami.Then they gave me my first formal inspection. At the completion of this inspection they went to a corner discussing something un know to me and then preceded to take all of my armor for the life of me I could not figure out what I had done wrong! They told me to stay where I was and left returning with four backpacks filled to the brim with a new set of bronze armor. I was shock and excited for this was the first time I had put on plate mail ... oh how I remember how heavy it was and how long it took them to fit all the leather straps and bindings to fit my slight frame. <br>
<br>
*smiles at the remembrance of lost friends<br>
<br>
When we were finally finished getting me into my armor Dami gave me two things, first was a dull circlet with small runes that I did not understand , and a mace that glowed with magical might that I knew would come in handy smiting those evil Crushbone Orcs! With thanks and a salute I then left with a huge smile upon my face and a new found vigor to spread the word of Tunare. For an uncounted number of moons I traveled Norrath bumping into a few of my brother and sister Knights in cities like Freeport, High Hold Keep, Kaladim, and Qyenos. In the Season of my fifth heal a wandering Minstral named Devarian Songslinger whom I had known and traveled with for many many seasons asked me if it was possible for me to be removed from my bonds as a Knight to help him in building another group of adventurers that were to be called The Platinum Dragons of Norrath. After a return to the Knights keep and a long discussion with my friends the Lady Jezeb , Sir Adjantis and Lord Dami I decided to join Devarien in his quest to build a group of adventurers. As I left the Knights Keep for what I thought Was the last time I turned and looked at my home of many seasons not knowing what the future might bring. Only knowing that my heart would always reside in the Knights Keep.<br>
<br>
Thus ending the Cleric Chronicles of Senben Strongfaith Volume One<br>
<br>
* rolls up the parchment and ties it with a small silk ribbon<br>
<br>
* pulls out a small figurine of Tunare and another Parchment<br>
<br>
Hail Lord Shamer<br>
<br>
 If I am ever needed whisper my name into this and I shall be by your side.<br>
<br>
Senben Strongfaith<br>
Knight of Freedom<br>
<br>
*wraps the Parchment around the Figurine <br>
<br>
* stands and calls the errand boy over<br>
<br>
Take this to Lord Shamer upon his return to the Keep and give him my apologies for not being around more often.<br>
<br>
* gathers his gear and leaves out the Keep gate<br>
<br>
See you soon friends!<br>
<br>
<br>
Senben Strongfaith<br>
Guide Officer<br>
